lass=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"| Points awarded to Portugal (Final)\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"| Televote\n|-\n!width=20%|12 points\n!width=20%|10 points\n!width=20%|8 points\n!width=20%|7 points\n!width=20%|6 points\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Austria|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Belgium|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Finland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|France|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Germany|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Iceland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Israel|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Lithuania|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Netherlands|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Norway|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Spain|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Switzerland|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Armenia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Croatia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Estonia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Ireland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Latvia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Poland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Sweden|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Ukraine|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Albania|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Azerbaijan|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Czech Republic|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Georgia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Greece|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Malta|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Montenegro|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Serbia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Slovenia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|United Kingdom|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Australia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Belarus|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Bulgaria|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Cyprus|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Hungary|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Macedonia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Romania|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|San Marino|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Moldova|y=2017}}\n|-\n!width=20%|5 points\n!width=20%|4 points\n!width=20%|3 points\n!width=20%|2 points\n!width=20%|1 point\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Denmark|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Italy|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"| Jury\n|-\n!width=20%|12 points\n!width=20%|10 points\n!width=20%|8 points\n!width=20%|7 points\n!width=20%|6 points\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Armenia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Czech Republic|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|France|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Georgia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Hungary|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Iceland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Israel|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Latvia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Lithuania|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Netherlands|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Poland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|San Marino|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Serbia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Slovenia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Spain|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Sweden|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Switzerland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|United Kingdom|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Belarus|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Denmark|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Germany|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Macedonia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Malta|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Norway|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Ukraine|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Austria|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Azerbaijan|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Belgium|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Cyprus|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Estonia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Finland|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Australia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Croatia|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Moldova|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Albania|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Romania|y=2017}}\n|-\n!width=20%|5 points\n!width=20%|4 points\n!width=20%|3 points\n!width=20%|2 points\n!width=20%|1 point\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{Esc|Greece|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Ireland|y=2017}}\n*{{Esc|Italy|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"| 50/50<ref name=\"Classic voting\"/>\n|-\n!width=20%|12 points\n!width=20%|10 points\n!width=20%|8 points\n!width=20%|7 points\n!width=20%|6 points\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* {{Esc|Armenia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Austria|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Belgium|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Czech Republic|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Estonia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Finland|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|France|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Germany|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Iceland|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Israel|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Lithuania|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Netherlands|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Norway|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|San Marino|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Slovenia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Spain|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Sweden|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Switzerland|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Ukraine|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|United Kingdom|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* {{Esc|Australia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Azerbaijan|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Belarus|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Denmark|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Georgia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Greece|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Hungary|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Latvia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Macedonia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Poland|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Serbia|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* {{Esc|Albania|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Croatia|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Italy|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Malta|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Romania|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* {{Esc|Cyprus|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Ireland|y=2017}}\n* {{Esc|Moldova|y=2017}}\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* {{Esc|Montenegro|y=2017}}\n|-\n!width=20%|5 points\n!width=20%|4 points\n!width=20%|3 points\n!width=20%|2 points\n!width=20%|1 point\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n| valign=\"top\" |\n|-\n|}\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response===\n\"Amar pelos dois\" received praise from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. Fabien Randanne of French newspaper ''[[20 minutes (France)|20 Minutes]]'' called \"Amar pelos dois\" a \"superb melancholic song\" and described it as a \"delightfully anachronistic sound\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.20minutes.fr/culture/2025335-20170306-video-eurovision-2017-portugal-fait-retour-superbe-chanson-melancolique |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306195314/http://www.20minutes.fr/culture/2025335-20170306-video-eurovision-2017-portugal-fait-retour-superbe-chanson-melancolique |title=Eurovision 2017: Le Portugal fait son retour avec une superbe chanson m\u00e9lancolique |work=[[20 minutes (France)|20 Minutes]] |author=F.R. |date=March 6, 2017 |archivedate=March 6, 2017 |language=fr |url-status=dead }}</ref> Francisco Chac\u00f3n of Spanish newspaper ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'' claimed that its jazz-pop tempo distinguished it from the \"outlandish proposals in the otherwise [[kitsch]] music scene\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.abc.es/cultura/eurovision/abci-eurovision-drama-humano-representante-portugal-eurovision-201703161856_noticia.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316195738/http://www.abc.es/cultura/eurovision/abci-eurovision-drama-humano-representante-portugal-eurovision-201703161856_noticia.html |title=El drama humano del representante de Portugal en Eurovisi\u00f3n |work=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]] |publisher=[[Grupo Vocento]] |author=Chac\u00f3n, Francisco |date=March 16, 2017 |archivedate=March 16, 2017 |language=es |url-status=dead }}</ref> French magazine ''[[Paris Match]]'' declared it as one of their ten favourite entries of the year, and noted a \"great vocal mastery\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parismatch.com/Culture/Medias/Eurovision-2017-nos-10-candidats-favoris-1222139 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329232135/http://www.parismatch.com/Culture/Medias/Eurovision-2017-nos-10-candidats-favoris-1222139 |title=Eurovision 2017 : nos 10 candidats favoris |work=[[Paris Match]] |publisher=Lagard\u00e8re Digital France |date=March 29, 2017 |archivedate=March 29, 2017 |language=fr |url-status=dead }}</ref> Chris Zeiher of Australian Eurovision broadcaster [[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]] noted the \"simplicity\" of the song, adding that \"there's something refreshing and reflective\" in it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/guide/article/2017/05/01/artists-eurovision-2017-salvador-sobral-amar-pelos-dois-portugal |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170504192628/http://www.sbs.com.au/guide/article/2017/05/01/artists-eurovision-2017-salvador-sobral-amar-pelos-dois-portugal |title=The artists of Eurovision 2017: Salvador Sobral \u2013 \"Amar pelos dois\" (Portugal) |work=[[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]] |author=Zeiher, Chris |date=May 2, 2017 |archivedate=May 4, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Benny Royston of British newspaper ''[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]'' named it \"Portugal's best ever Eurovision entry\", and commented that \"sticking to [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] maintains the charm and charisma of this song that pulls at the heartstrings through musical composition\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/05/04/the-world-is-falling-in-love-with-portugals-best-ever-eurovision-entry-6615823/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170504212202/http://metro.co.uk/2017/05/04/the-world-is-falling-in-love-with-portugals-best-ever-eurovision-entry-6615823/ |title=The world is falling in love with Portugal\u2019s best ever Eurovision entry |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |publisher=[[DMG Media]] |author=Royston, Benny |date=May 4, 2017 |archivedate=May 4, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Christopher D. Shea of American newspaper ''[[The New York Times]]'' described it as an \"unexpectedly earnest ballad\" that \"has earned a loyal following for upending over-the-top Eurovision expectations\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/08/arts/music/eurovision-song-contest-2017-guide.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509230251/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/08/arts/music/eurovision-song-contest-2017-guide.html|title=From Crimean Conflict to \u2018Yodel It!,\u2019 a Guide to Eurovision 2017|work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|author=D. Shea, Christopher|date=May 8, 2017|archivedate=May 9, 2017|access-date=April 25, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Richard van de Crommert of Dutch newspaper ''[[De Telegraaf]]'' considered it Portugal's all-time best Eurovision entry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/prive/28130148/__Handleiding_voor_Kiev__.html |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170901223529/http://www.telegraaf.nl/prive/28130148/__Handleiding_voor_Kiev__.html |title=D\u00edt moet je weten voor de halve finale ESF |work=[[De Telegraaf]] |publisher=[[Telegraaf Media Groep]] |author=van de Crommert, Richard |date=May 9, 2017 |archivedate=2017-09-01 |language=nl |access-date=2017-09-01 |url-status=live }}</ref> Jens Maier of German magazine ''[[Stern (magazine)|Stern]]'' called the song a \"surprise\", adding that it \"enchanted\" the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2017|contest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stern.de/kultur/musik/esc--ein-portugiese-verzaubert-kiew---so-lief-das-erste-semifinale-7446834.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170626233014/http://www.stern.de/kultur/musik/esc--ein-portugiese-verzaubert-kiew---so-lief-das-erste-semifinale-7446834.html |title=Ein Portugiese verzaubert den ESC \u2013 so lief das erste Semifinale |work=[[Stern (magazine)|Stern]] |publisher=[[Gruner + Jahr]] |author=Maier, Jens |date=May 10, 2017 |archivedate=June 26, 2017 |language=de |url-status=dead }}</ref> Charlotte Runcie of British newspaper ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' described it as an \"artistic, beautifully crafted\" and \"sophisticated\" song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2017/05/09/eurovision-semi-final-one-live-results-running-order/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170511055313/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2017/05/09/eurovision-semi-final-one-live-results-running-order/ |title=Eurovision 2017, semi final 1 recap: let's all do the saxophone dance, and other highlights |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |author=Runcie, Charlotte |date=May 11, 2017 |archivedate=May 11, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n=== Commercial performance ===\n\"Amar pelos dois\" achieved [[Record chart|commercial success]], particularly in [[Europe]]. In Portugal, \"Amar pelos dois\" reached number 1 on the singles chart following its victory in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2017]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://portuguesecharts.com/archive.asp?todo=show&woche=20&jahr=2017&sparte=s|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170601003506/http://portuguesecharts.com/archive.asp?todo=show&woche=20&jahr=2017&sparte=s|title=Portuguese Charts: Singles|publisher=Hung Medien|archivedate=June 1, 2017}}</ref> On the Portuguese download chart, the song debuted at number 4, after winning the national final [[Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o]]. In the following week, it climbed to number 3,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2017-04-01/portugal |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170403231120/http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2017-04-01/portugal |title=Portugal Digital Song Sales |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=April 1, 2017 |archivedate=April 3, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and topped the chart eventually.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2017-05-27/portugal |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170519111334/http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2017-05-27/portugal |title=Portugal Digital Song Sales |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=May 27, 2017 |archivedate=May 19, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> It was certified gold by the [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica Portuguesa]] (AFP), selling over 7,500 units.<ref name=\"Certification\">{{cite tweet|user=ESC_Portugal|number=872584241141473280|date=June 7, 2017|title=\"Amar pelos dois\" alcan\u00e7a disco de ouro|language=pt}}</ref> In Portugal, \"Amar pelos dois\" broke the record held by [[Ed Sheeran]]'s \"[[Shape of You]]\" for the most [[Streaming media|streams]] ever in a single day on [[Spotify]], with 75,373 daily streams, and became the only song to cross the 60,000 mark in a 24-hour period.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spotifycharts.com/regional/pt/daily/2017-05-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804222942/https://spotifycharts.com/regional/pt/daily/2017-05-14|title=Spotify Charts - Portugal|work=[[Spotify]]|date=May 14, 2017|archivedate=August 4, 2017}}</ref> Also on home ground, it achieved the second-biggest week ever for Spotify streams, with 366,423 weekly streams, and became one of only three songs to cross the 300,000 mark in a 7-day period.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spotifycharts.com/regional/pt/weekly/2017-05-12--2017-05-19|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804222306/https://spotifycharts.com/regional/pt/weekly/2017-05-12--2017-05-19|title=Spotify Charts - Portugal|work=[[Spotify]]|date=May 18, 2017|archivedate=August 4, 2017}}</ref> \n\nIn the rest of Europe, \"Amar pelos dois\" appeared on several download charts, reaching number 1 in Finland and the Netherlands, number 3 in Luxembourg, Norway and Sweden, number 4 in Denmark, number 5 in Greece, number 6 in Belgium, and number 31 in the [[UK Singles Downloads Chart|United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.fi/tilastot/virallinen-lista/artistit/Salvador+Sobral/Amar+pelos+dois |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170529185457/http://www.ifpi.fi/tilastot/virallinen-lista/artistit/Salvador%2BSobral/Amar%2Bpelos%2Bdois |title=Tilastot - Suomen virallinen lista - Artistit |publisher=[[Musiikkituottajat \u2013 IFPI Finland]] |archivedate=May 29, 2017 |language=fi |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"Billboard2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ts_chart_artistname%3Asalvador%20sobral&f[1]=ss_bb_type%3Achart_item&type=2&artist=salvador%20sobral |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170603121748/http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D=ts_chart_artistname:salvador%20sobral&f%5B1%5D=ss_bb_type:chart_item&type=2&artist=salvador%20sobral |title=Chart Search |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archivedate=June 3, 2017 |accessdate=May 19, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-downloads-chart/20170519/7000/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170529200504/http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-downloads-chart/20170519/7000/ |title=Official Singles Downloads Chart Top 100 |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |archivedate=May 29, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On other singles charts, the song peaked at number 1 in Iceland, number 6 in Switzerland, number 8 in Hungary, and number 22 in Austria.<ref name=\"Iceland\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ruv.is/lag/amar-pelos-dois |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180821193145/http://www.ruv.is/lag/amar-pelos-dois |title=R\u00daV - Vins\u00e6ldalisti R\u00e1sar 2 |publisher=[[R\u00daV]] |archivedate=2018-08-21 |accessdate=May 20, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitparade.ch/charts/singles/21-05-2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170605211535/http://hitparade.ch/charts/singles/21-05-2017|title=Schweizer Hitparade - Singles Top 100|publisher=Hung Medien|date=May 21, 2017|archivedate=June 5, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://zene.slagerlistak.hu/single-track-top-40-lista/2017/20 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170529202440/http://zene.slagerlistak.hu/single-track-top-40-lista/2017/20 |title=Single (track) Top 40 lista |publisher=[[Association of Hungarian Record Companies|Magyar Hanglemezkiad\u00f3k Sz\u00f6vets\u00e9ge]] |archivedate=May 29, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://austriancharts.at/charts/singles/26-05-2017|title=Austria Top 40 - Singles|publisher=Hung Medien|date=May 26, 2017}}</ref> In France, it reached number 4, achieving the highest position for a [[Eurovision Song Contest]] winning entry since the {{Esccnty|United Kingdom|y=1976}}'s \"[[Save Your Kisses for Me]]\" in {{Escyr|1976}}.<ref name=\"France\">{{cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles-telecharges/?ye=2017&we=20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170529191451/http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles-telecharges/?ye=2017&we=20|title=Le Top de la semaine : Top Singles T\u00e9l\u00e9charg\u00e9s|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]]|date=May 19, 2017|archivedate=May 29, 2017|access-date=May 19, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In Spain, \"Amar pelos dois\" debuted at number 1 and became the first Eurovision Song Contest winning entry to reach the top spot since {{Esccnty|Israel|y=1998}}'s \"[[Diva (Dana International song)|Diva]]\" in {{Escyr|1998}}.<ref name=\"Spain\">{{cite web|url=http://spanishcharts.com/weekchart.asp?cat=s3&year=2017&date=20170521|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421190216/http://spanishcharts.com/weekchart.asp?cat=s3&year=2017&date=20170521|title=Physical/Digital Single Top 50|publisher=Hung Medien|date=May 21, 2017|archivedate=April 21, 2018}}</ref> In regard to streaming, the song achieved the third-biggest day ever on Spotify in Lithuania, with 5,704 daily streams.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spotifycharts.com/regional/lt/daily/2017-05-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170901231929/https://spotifycharts.com/regional/lt/daily/2017-05-14|title=Spotify Charts - Lithuania|work=[[Spotify]]|date=May 14, 2017|archivedate=September 1, 2017}}</ref> \n\nIn the United States, \"Amar pelos dois\" peaked at number 7 on the [[Billboard_charts#International_charts|World Digital Songs]] chart, as one of the best-performing international digital singles.<ref name=\"Billboard2\"/>\n\nIn 2017, \"Amar pelos dois\" was listed at number 1 on the official [[Eurovision Song Contest]] year-end chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ouJYJWEx8l8|title=TOP 50: Most watched in 2017: 10 TO 1 - Eurovision Song Contest|website=[[YouTube]]|date=December 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\n\"Amar pelos dois\" earned the Sobral siblings two [[Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Awards]]. Salvador Sobral received the Artistic Award, whereas Lu\u00edsa Sobral received the Composer Award.<ref name=\"Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Awards\">{{cite web|url=http://media.rtp.pt/festivaldacancao/artigos/marcel-bezencon-award-portugal-ganha-premio-artistico-e-premio-de-compositor-por-amar-pelos-dois/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170513191625/http://media.rtp.pt/festivaldacancao/artigos/marcel-bezencon-award-portugal-ganha-premio-artistico-e-premio-de-compositor-por-amar-pelos-dois/ |title=Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Award: Portugal ganha pr\u00e9mio art\u00edstico e pr\u00e9mio de compositor por \"Amar pelos dois\" |work=[[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal|RTP]] |date=May 13, 2017 |archivedate=May 13, 2017 |language=pt |url-status=dead }}</ref> It marked the first time an entry was recognised with two of these awards since the {{Esccnty|Netherlands|y=2014}}' \"[[Calm After the Storm]]\" ({{Escyr|2014}}). \n\nAt the ESC Radio Awards, \"Amar pelos dois\" won Best Song. It marked the first time since {{Esccnty|Sweden|y=2012}}'s \"[[Euphoria (Loreen song)|Euphoria]]\" ({{Escyr|2012}}) that a Eurovision Song Contest winning entry also topped the ESC Radio Awards poll. Additionally, the song earned Salvador Sobral the Best Male Artist award.<ref name=\"ESC Radio Awards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.escradio.com/2017/06/esc-radio-awards-2017-the-winners/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170724231509/http://www.escradio.com/2017/06/esc-radio-awards-2017-the-winners/|title=ESC Radio Awards 2017 \u2013 The Winners|last=Mourinho|first=Daniel|website=ESC Radio|date=June 12, 2017|archivedate= July 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2017\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Awards]]<ref name=\"Marcel Bezen\u00e7on Awards\"/>\n|Artistic Award\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Composer Award\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|ESC Radio Awards<ref name=\"ESC Radio Awards\"/>\n|Best Song\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Male Artist\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2018\n|rowspan=\"1\"|SPA Awards<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spautores.pt/destaques/premio-autores-2018-vencedores|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20180321235646/https://www.spautores.pt/destaques/premio-autores-2018-vencedores|title=Pr\u00e9mio Autores 2018 / Vencedores|website=Sociedade Portuguesa de Autores|date=March 20, 2018|archivedate=March 21, 2018|language=pt}}</ref>\n|Best Song in Popular Music\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Golden Globes (Portugal)]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sic.sapo.pt/Programas/globosdeourosic/musica/2018-05-21-Amar-Pelos-Dois-e-a-Melhor-Musica-de-2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180523211455/http://sic.sapo.pt/Programas/globosdeourosic/musica/2018-05-21-Amar-Pelos-Dois-e-a-Melhor-Musica-de-2017|title=\u2018Amar Pelos Dois\u2019 \u00e9 a Melhor M\u00fasica de 2017|website=[[Sociedade Independente de Comunica\u00e7\u00e3o|SIC]]|date=May 21, 2018|archivedate=May 23, 2018|language=pt}}</ref>\n|Best Song \n|{{won}}\n|}\n\n==Live performances==\nSalvador Sobral and his sister Lu\u00edsa Sobral, composer of \"Amar pelos dois\", first appeared on the radio stations [[RFM (Portuguese radio station)|RFM]] (8 March 2017) and [[R\u00e1dio Comercial]] (14 March 2017).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lAwyAs8GVDM|title=AMAR PELOS DOIS - Salvador Sobral e Lu\u00edsa Sobral|website=[[YouTube]]|date=March 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vHqdXANF85c|title=R\u00e1dio Comercial / Salvador Sobral - Amar Pelos Dois|website=[[YouTube]]|date=March 14, 2017}}</ref> On 2 May 2017, Salvador Sobral's performance for ''Spain Calling International'' became available on [[RTVE]]'s website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtve.es/alacarta/videos/eurovision-2017/eurovision-2017-salvador-sobral-portugal-interpreta-directo-amar-pelos-dois/3998491/|title=Eurovisi\u00f3n 2017 - Salvador Sobral (Portugal) interpreta en directo \"Amar Pelos Dois\"|website=[[RTVE]]|date=May 2, 2017|language=es}}</ref> On 25 May 2017, the Sobral siblings performed on [[RTP1]]'s [[talk show]] ''Agora N\u00f3s''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.rtp.pt/festivaldacancao/videos/salvador-luisa-sobral-cantam-amar-pelos-dois-no-agora-nos/|title=Salvador e Lu\u00edsa Sobral cantam \u201cAmar Pelos Dois\u201d no Agora N\u00f3s|website=[[Radio and Television of Portugal|RTP]]|date=May 25, 2017|language=pt}}</ref> On 12 May 2018, Salvador Sobral performed alongside Brazilian singer [[Caetano Veloso]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0aomcisD48I|title=Salvador Sobral performs with Caetano Veloso at the Grand Final of the 2018 Eurovision Song Contest|website=[[YouTube]]|date=May 12, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Legacy==\n===European Union Songbook===\n\"Amar pelos dois\" was included in the [[European Union]] Songbook as the all-time top Portuguese [[love song]]. \"Amar pelos dois\" was the most voted by the public in a field of ten songs pre-selected by music professionals, thus representing Portugal in the category Love.<ref name=\"EU Songbook\">{{cite web|url=http://www.eu-songbook.org/chosen-songs/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114205114/http://www.eu-songbook.org/chosen-songs/|title=Chosen songs|website=European Union Songbook|archivedate=November 14, 2018|accessdate=November 14, 2018|}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc;\"\n! Country\n! Category\n! Song\n! Result\n|- style=\"background:gold;\"\n| {{POR}}\n| [[Love song|Love]]\n| \"Amar pelos dois\"\n| 1st\n|}\n\n== Use in media ==\n\"Amar pelos dois\" is the opening theme song for the Brazilian [[telenovela]] ''[[Tempo de Amar]]'' on [[Rede Globo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.movenoticias.com/2017/08/amar-pelos-dois-salvador-sobral-vai-tema-novela-da-globo/ |title='Amar pelos dois' de Salvador Sobral vai ser tema de novela da Globo|website=Move Not\u00edcias|date=August 1, 2017|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IqlRVa42RmE|title=Tempo de Amar: veja a abertura|website=[[YouTube]]|date=September 26, 2017}}</ref> \"Amar pelos dois\" generated a two-part [[television documentary]] titled ''Sem Fazer Planos do Que Vir\u00e1 Depois'' and aired by Portuguese broadcaster [[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal|RTP]]. As the central theme, \"Amar pelos dois\" is played and sung throughout the documentary.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://media.rtp.pt/agoranos/artigos/sem-planos-do-vira-vitoria-salvador-sobral|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231010052/http://media.rtp.pt/agoranos/artigos/sem-planos-do-vira-vitoria-salvador-sobral|title=\u201cSem fazer planos do que vir\u00e1 depois\u201d: a vit\u00f3ria de Salvador Sobral|website=[[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal]]|archivedate=December 31, 2017|language=pt}}</ref> \n\n== Cover versions ==\n{{multiple image\n | footer = [[Eurovision Song Contest]] winners [[Marie Myriam]] (''left'') and [[Alexander Rybak]] (''right'') covered \"Amar pelos dois\".\n | image1 = MarieMyriam.jpg\n | image2 = Alexander Rybak i Skien (1).jpg\n | align  = right\n}}\n\n* [[Alexander Rybak]], [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]] winner for {{Esccnty|Norway|y=2009}}, recorded an English-language version.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FNd3tyY7CcA|title=Alexander Rybak - ESC Winner 2017 Portugal - Tribute Cover (UNOFFICIAL English Lyrics)|website=[[YouTube]]|date=May 14, 2017}}</ref> \n* [[Nathan Trent]], {{Esccnty|Austria|y=2017}}'s representative in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2017]], did a rendition of the song with the Tiroler Symphonie Orchestra in his hometown, [[Innsbruck]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=upTrent|number=882201872886530049|date=July 4, 2017|title=A snippet of yesterday's performance of \"Amar Pelos Dois\" with orchestra! I had so much fun! Hope you guys like it :)}}</ref> Trent performed it again at the Eurovision Live Concert 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=67UHSDnFB1k|title=Nathan Trent - Amar pelos dois|website=[[YouTube]]|date=September 9, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Selma Bj\u00f6rnsd\u00f3ttir]], {{Esccnty|Iceland}}'s representative in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1999]] and [[Eurovision Song Contest 2005|2005]], covered the song in English language at Eurobash 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mlQHb2-qmNg|title=Selma - Amar Pelos Dois - English version of Portugal 2017 - Eurovision|website=[[YouTube]]|date=September 14, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Lea Sirk]], {{Esccnty|Slovenia|y=2018}}'s representative in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]], performed the song on the [[talent show]] ''[[Your Face Sounds Familiar (Slovenian TV series)|Znan obraz ima svoj glas]]'', the Slovenian version of ''[[Your Face Sounds Familiar]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PvHCNhpTlM0|title=Your Face Sounds Familiar S4 E1 (SLOVENIA) - Salvador Sobral (Lea Sirk) - Amar Pelos Dois|website=[[YouTube]]|date=September 24, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Laura Groeseneken]], {{Esccnty|Belgium|y=2018}}'s representative in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, covered the song in English language on the [[talk show]] ''Van Gils & gasten''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HE6RzSCDjgw|title=Laura Groeseneken met Love for Both - Cover version 'Amar Pelos Dois' by Salvador Sobral|website=[[YouTube]]|date=September 28, 2017}}</ref>\n* Dutch singer [[Jim van der Zee]], winner of the [[The Voice of Holland (season 8)|eighth season]] of singing competition ''[[The Voice of Holland]]'', covered the song in English language.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SAqOtZjEZRY|title=Jim van der Zee - Amar Pelos Dois / The voice of Holland / The Blind Auditions / Season 8|website=[[YouTube]]|date=October 20, 2017}}</ref>\n* Actor [[:es:Miquel Fern\u00e1ndez|Miquel Fern\u00e1ndez]] performed the song on the talent show ''[[:es:Tu cara me suena|Tu cara me suena]]'', the Spanish edition of ''Your Face Sounds Familiar''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=72Ve_V672LM|title=Miquel Fern\u00e1ndez imita a Salvador Sobral con 'Amar pelos dois' - Tu Cara Me Suena|website=[[YouTube]]|date=October 28, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Florin Cezar Ouatu|Cezar]], {{Esccnty|Romania|y=2013}}'s representative in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2013]], performed the song on the talent show ''[[Te cunosc de undeva!]]'', the Romanian version of ''Your Face Sounds Familiar''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PLnLU87vJ8w|title=Cezar Ouatu se transform\u0103 \u00een Salvador Sobral - Amar pelos dois|website=[[YouTube]]|date=November 4, 2017}}</ref> Cezar also covered the song in [[Selec\u021bia Na\u021bional\u0103]], [[Romania in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|Romania]]'s national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GaVzdDAnUZA|title=Cezar Ouatu - Amar pelos dois / Finala Eurovision Rom\u00e2nia 2018|website=[[YouTube]]|date=February 27, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Alfred Garc\u00eda]], {{Esccnty|Spain|y=2018}}'s representative in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, performed the song in the [[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (series 9)|ninth season]] of Spanish [[reality television]] [[talent show]] ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spanish TV series)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-XswOUMP83g|title=\"Amar Pelos Dois\u201d - Alfred / Gala 4 / OT 2017|website=[[YouTube]]|date=November 20, 2017}}</ref>\n* Portuguese group Spell Choir recorded an [[a cappella]] version of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vMnz--MG6_A|title=Spell Choir - Amar pelos Dois|website=[[YouTube]]|date=November 30, 2017}}</ref>\n* Yurcash, runners-up of the [[X Factor (Ukraine series 8)|eighth season]] of Ukraine's music competition ''[[X-Factor (Ukrainian TV series)|X-Factor]]'', did a Ukrainian-language cover of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eVYbIXAKP5k|title=\u0413\u0440\u0443\u043f\u043f\u0430 Yurcash \u2013 Salvador Sobral \u2013 Amar Pelos Dois \u2013 \u0425-\u0424\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 8. \u0427\u0435\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0442\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e\u0439 \u044d\u0444\u0438\u0440|website=[[YouTube]]|date=December 2, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Marie Myriam]], [[Eurovision Song Contest 1977]] winner for {{Esccnty|France|y=1977}}, covered the song in Destination Eurovision, [[France in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|France]]'s national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bi423UtEYts|title=Medley jury + Marie Myriam - Amar Pelos Dois / Salvador Sobral|website=[[YouTube]]|date=January 20, 2018}}</ref>\n* Portuguese singer Ricardo Caria did a rendition of the song in Selec\u021bia Na\u021bional\u0103, Romania's national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MBOWqow3aJ4|title=Ricardo Caria interpreta \"Amar Pelos Dois\" no Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o da Rom\u00e9nia|website=[[YouTube]]|date=January 28, 2018}}</ref>\n* Swiss-Portuguese singer Let\u00edcia Carvalho performed the song alongside Appenzeller S\u00e4ngerfreunde in Die Entscheidungsshow, [[Switzerland in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|Switzerland]]'s national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nmzRveCHLEQ|title=Leticia und Appenzeller S\u00e4ngerfreunde - Showact - \u00abAmar Pelos Dois\u00bb|website=[[YouTube]]|date=February 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* Sigr\u00ed\u00f0ur Thorlacius and Valdimar Gu\u00f0mundsson did an Icelandic-language cover of the song in [[Iceland_in_the_Eurovision_Song_Contest_2018#S%C3%B6ngvakeppnin_2018|S\u00f6ngvakeppnin]], Iceland's national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hWR257jPutk|title=\u00c1st fyrir tvo (Amar Pelos Dois) \u2013 Sigr\u00ed\u00f0ur Thorlacius og Valdimar Gu\u00f0mundsson|website=[[YouTube]]|date=February 26, 2018}}</ref>\n* Ukrainian singer [[Tayanna]] covered the song in [[Eurovision National Selection (Ukraine)|Vidbir]], [[Ukraine in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|Ukraine]]'s national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xF4Wm7d5MNI|title=\u0424\u0456\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0441\u043f\u0456\u0432\u0430\u044e\u0442\u044c \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0443\u0440\u0456 \u0445\u0456\u0442\u0456\u0432 \u0404\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f|website=[[YouTube]]|date=February 24, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Ari \u00d3lafsson]], {{Esccnty|Iceland|y=2018}}'s representative in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, did a bilingual English/Portuguese cover of the song.<ref>{{Facebook|ariolafsAIRmusic/posts/1675629242476484|name=Ari \u00d3lafsson}}