iziana Tosca Donati]], winner of the [[Sanremo Music Festival 1996]], recorded an Italian-language version for her album ''Morabeza''.<ref>{{Facebook|TizianaToscaDonatiOfficial/videos/10156716253803896/|name=Tiziana Tosca Donati}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DMR7vP8vpNc|title=Per ogni oggi che verr\u00e0|website=[[YouTube]]|date=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[:cs:Jitka Zelenkov\u00e1|Jitka Zelenkov\u00e1]] recorded a Czech-language version for her album ''Intimity''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YYShNSaHgzk|title=L\u00e1ska za oba (Amar pelos dois)|website=[[YouTube]]|date=October 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Arisa]], winner of the [[Sanremo Music Festival 2014]], recorded an Italian-language version for her album ''Una nuova Rosalba in citt\u00e0''.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.allmusicitalia.it/news/arisa-mi-sento-bene-sobral.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111234340/http://www.allmusicitalia.it/news/arisa-mi-sento-bene-sobral.html|title=Arisa nel nuovo album anche una canzone di Salvador Sobral, vincitore dell\u2019Eurovision 2017|website=All Music Italia|date=January 5, 2019|archivedate=January 11, 2019|language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v7FdBQS-TwA|title=Amarsi in due|website=[[YouTube]]|date=February 25, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jelena Toma\u0161evi\u0107]], {{Esccnty|Serbia|y=2008}}'s representative in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008]], and Lea Sirk, Slovenia's representative in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018, covered the song in [[Beovizija]], Serbia's national selection for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2019]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NNi-yFkivZY|title=Jelena Toma\u0161evi\u0107 i Lea Sirk - Amar pelos dois / Beovizija 2019|website=[[YouTube]]|date=March 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jurijus Veklenko]], {{Esccnty|Lithuania|y=2019}}'s representative in the Eurovision Song Contest 2019, covered the song.<ref>{{Instagram|p/BvudnlngRJq|name=Jurijus Veklenko}}</ref>\n* Actor [[:el:\u0391\u03c1\u03b3\u03cd\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03b3\u03b3\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5|Argyris Angelou]] performed the song on the [[Your Face Sounds Familiar (Greek TV series)|Greek version]] of talent show ''Your Face Sounds Familiar''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BunC_ok5MZ0|title=YFSF 5: 11\u03bf Live - \u0391\u03c1\u03b3\u03cd\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 \u0391\u03b3\u03b3\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5 (Salvador Sobral - Amar Pelos Dois) {7/4/2019}|website=[[YouTube]]|date=April 7, 2019}}</ref>\n* Spanish singer [[Pablo Albor\u00e1n]] did a rendition of the song during his concert in [[Lisbon]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.escportugal.pt/2019/06/video-pablo-alboran-canta-amar-pelos.html|title=Pablo Albor\u00e1n canta \"Amar Pelos Dois\" no Campo Pequeno|website=ESC Portugal|date=June 29, 2019|language=pt}}</ref>\n* [[Mar\u00eda Villal\u00f3n]], winner of the first season of music competition ''[[Factor X (Spanish TV series)|Factor X]]'' (Spanish version of ''[[The X Factor]]'') and the seventh season of talent show ''Tu cara me suena'' (Spanish edition of ''Your Face Sounds Familiar''), covered the song during her concert in [[:es:La Cueva de El Gato|La Cueva del Gato]], [[Province of M\u00e1laga|M\u00e1laga]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BAEHI__Kygs|title=Mar\u00eda Villal\u00f3n versiona \"Amar pelos dois\" en La Cueva del Gato (Benaoj\u00e1n-Espa\u00f1a)|website=[[YouTube]]|date=July 21, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Seraf\u00edn Zubiri]], {{Esccnty|Spain}}'s representative in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1992]] and [[Eurovision Song Contest 2000|2000]], covered the song at the 14th [[OGAE]] Spain convention.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OeLNbl5m3rA|title=Seraf\u00edn Zubiri - \u201cAmar Pelos Dois\u201d - XIV Congreso de OGAE Espa\u00f1a|website=[[YouTube]]|date=October 8, 2019}}</ref>\n* Estonian operatic tenor [[:et:Oliver Kuusik|Oliver Kuusik]] covered the song in [[Eesti Laul]], Estonia's national selection for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2020]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-746ZiUCuQM|title=Oliver Kuusik - Amar Pelos Dois and Arcade (Eesti Laul 2020 II poolfinaal)|website=[[YouTube]]|date=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Track listings ==\n* '''Digital download'''<ref name=\"iTunes\"/>\n# \"Amar pelos dois\" \u2013 3:05\n\n* '''CD single'''<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=Amar pelos dois (Liner Notes)|others=Salvador Sobral|date=June 16, 2017|type=Compact Disc|publisher=Sons em Tr\u00e2nsito}}</ref>\n# \"Amar pelos dois\" \u2013 3:05\n# \"Amar pelos dois\" (Instrumental) \u2013 2:56\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\n* Salvador Sobral \u2013 [[Lead vocalist|Vocals]]\n* Lu\u00edsa Sobral \u2013 [[Record producer|Production]], [[Songwriter|songwriting]]\n* Lu\u00eds Figueiredo \u2013 [[Arrangement|String arrangement]], [[piano]]<ref name=\"escportugal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.escportugal.pt/2017/01/entrevista-luisa-sobral-quis-fazer-uma.html|title=[ENTREVISTA] Lu\u00edsa Sobral: \"Quis fazer uma can\u00e7\u00e3o bonita para o Festival da Can\u00e7\u00e3o\"|website=ESC Portugal|date=January 18, 2017|language=pt}}</ref>\n* Quarteto Arabesco \u2013 [[Violin family|Strings]]<ref name=\"escportugal\"/>\n\nCredits adapted from the liner notes of \"Amar pelos dois\" promo single.<ref>{{cite AV media notes |title=Amar pelos dois (Liner Notes)|others=Salvador Sobral|year=2017|type=Compact Disc|work=MarteRecords promo|publisher=Sons em Tr\u00e2nsito}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|22|artist=Salvador Sobral|song=Amar pelos dois|rowheader=true|accessdate=25 May 2017}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|30|artist=Salvador Sobral|song=Amar pelos dois|rowheader=true|accessdate=19 May 2017}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|8|artist=Salvador Sobral|song=Amar pelos 