ode 7\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|1|12|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 465a68\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 29\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = Episode 8\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|1|19|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 465a68\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 30\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 9\n| Title           = Episode 9\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|1|26|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 465a68\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = Episode 10\n| DirectedBy      = \n| WrittenBy       = \n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|2|2|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 465a68\n}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://areena.yle.fi/1-3677300}}\n* {{IMDb title|tt4937942}}\n\n[[Category:2016 Finnish television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s crime television series]]\n[[Category:Finnish drama television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|Bordertown (disambiguation){{!}}Bordertown}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Bordertown\n| image                = Sorjonen-title.jpg\n| caption              = Finnish title card\n| native_name          = Sorjonen\n| genre                = {{Plainlist|\n* Crime drama\n* Nordic noir\n}}\n| creator              = Miikko Oikkonen\n| developer            =\n| writer               =\n| director             = {{Plainlist|\n* Miikko Oikkonen\n* Jyri K\u00e4h\u00f6nen\n* Juuso Syrj\u00e4\n}}\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ville Virtanen (actor)|Ville Virtanen]]\n* [[Matleena Kuusniemi]]\n* [[Anu Sinisalo]]\n* [[Lenita Susi]]\n* [[Kristiina Halttu]]\n* [[Olivia Ainali]]\n* [[Ilkka Villi]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer =\n| opentheme            =\n| endtheme             =\n| composer             =\n| country              = Finland\n| language             = Finnish\n| num_seasons          = 3 <!--Increment when new seasons/series begin.-->\n| num_episodes         = 31 <!--Increment only when a new episode airs \u2014 unless all episodes are released on same day.-->\n| list_episodes        =\n| executive_producer   =\n| producer             =\n| editor               =\n| location             =\n| cinematography       =\n| camera               = \n| runtime              = 58 minutes\n| company              = {{Plainlist|\n* Fisher King Production\n* Federation Entertainment\n}}\n| distributor          = <!--Original distribution company or companies-->\n| network              = [[Yle TV1]]\n| picture_format       = 16:9 ([[1080i50]])\n| audio_format         = 2.0 surround\n| first_run            =\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2016|10|16|df=y}} \u2013 present\n| last_aired           = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} -->\n| preceded_by          =\n| followed_by          =\n| related              =\n| website              = https://areena.yle.fi/1-3677300\n| website_title        = The series on Yle TV1\n| production_website    =\n| production_website_title =\n}}\n'''''Bordertown''''' ({{lang-fi|'''Sorjonen'''}}) is a Finnish [[crime drama]] and [[Nordic noir]] television series created by Miikko Oikkonen and starring [[Ville Virtanen (actor)|Ville Virtanen]] as Detective Inspector Kari Sorjonen. It premiered in Finland on 16 October 2016 on [[Yle TV1]]. The series was renewed for a second season on 25 April 2017. Season 2 premiered on 7 October 2018. It was renewed for a third season in September 2018. Season 3 is set to premiere in December 2019.\n\n==Plot==\nDetective Inspector Kari Sorjonen is one of the most respected officers at the [[National Bureau of Investigation (Finland)|National Bureau of Investigation]] in Finland when his wife barely survives brain cancer. Sorjonen then takes a new job leading SECRI, the Serious Crime Unit in [[Lappeenranta]], and moves his family to the town near the border of Russia for a more peaceful life. But life turns out to be less than peaceful there.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n<!-- Cast names in opening credits and same order as seen in credits. -->\n{{divcol}}\n* [[Ville Virtanen (actor)|Ville Virtanen]] as Detective Inspector Kari Sorjonen\n* [[Matleena Kuusniemi]] as Pauliina Sorjonen\n* [[Anu Sinisalo]] as Detective Constable Lena Jaakkola\n* [[Lenita Susi]] as Katia Jaakkola\n* [[Kristiina Halttu]] as Detective Superintendent Taina Perttula\n* [[Olivia Ainali]] as Janina Sorjonen\n* [[Ilkka Villi]] as Detective Constable Niko Uusitalo\n{{divcolend}}\n\n===Recurring===\n<!-- Cast names in closing credits \u2013 in same order of who is billed first in each ascending episode. -->\n{{divcol}}\n* [[:fi:Max Bremer|Max Bremer]] as Coroner Hannu-Pekka Lund\n* [[:fi:Matti Laine|Matti Laine]] as Risto Susi-Huhtala\n* [[:fi:Jasmin Hamid|Jasmin Hamid]] as Jenna \"J\u00e4nis\" Luhta\n* [[:fi:Janne Virtanen|Janne Virtanen]] as Robert Degerman\n* [[Mikko Leppilampi]] as Mikael Ahola\n* [[Laura Malmivaara]] as Anneli Ahola\n* [[:fi:Niina Nurminen|Niina Nurminen]] as Johanna Metso\n* [[:fi:Elias Salonen|Elias Salonen]] as Elias Str\u00f6m\n* Eriikka V\u00e4liahde as Satu-Maria Porttila\n* [[:fi:Svante Martin|Svante Martin]] as G\u00f6sta Liljeqvist\n* [[:fi:Satu Paavola|Satu Paavola]] as Veera Niemi\n* [[:fi:Maria Kuusiluoma|Maria Kuusiluoma]] as Jaana Erkki  \n* [[:fi:Johan Storg\u00e5rd|Johan Storg\u00e5rd]] as Tuomas Heikkinen\n* [[:fi:Robert Enckell|Robert Enckell]] as Paul Degerman\n{{divcolend}}\n\n==Development and production==\n\n''Bordertown'' is produced for [[Yle]] by Fisher King Production<ref name=fisher>{{cite web|title=Bordertown|url=https://www.fisherking.fi/projects/bordertown/|website=Fisher King Oy|date=2017|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref> and Federation Entertainment.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bordertown|url=http://fedent.com/bordertown/|website=Federation Entertainment|date=2017 |accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=dramaquarterly>{{cite web|title=Nordic Noir gets a lighter Finnish|url=http://dramaquarterly.com/nordic-noir-gets-a-lighter-finnish/|website=Drama Quarterly|date=July 28, 2016|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=keslassy>{{cite web|last1=Keslassy|first1=Elsa|title=Federation, Fisher King Team on Nordic Noir Series \u2018Bordertown\u2019|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/global/federation-fisher-king-team-on-nordic-noir-series-bordertown-1201726405/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 9, 2016|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=hopewell>{{cite web|first=John|last=Hopewell|title=\u2018Marseille\u2019s\u2019 Pascal Breton on \u2018Bordertown,\u2019 Nordic Noir, Big Euro Co-pros and Crucial Change in Intl. TV (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/markets-festivals/marseille-pascal-breton-bordertown-nordic-noir-big-euro-co-pros-1201744288/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 2, 2016|accessdate=1 December 2017}}</ref> The series was presented at the [[MIPTV Media Market]] in Cannes on 3 April 2016, where it competed in the MIPDrama Screenings for the \"Coup de C\u0153ur\" award.<ref name=ttvnews>{{cite web|title=Bordertown is coming to MipTV|url=http://www.todotvnews.com/news/bordertown-is-coming-to-miptv.html|website=ttvnews|publisher=TodotvMedia|date=March 10, 2016|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=federation>{{cite web|title=Federation taking buyers to Bordertown|url=https://tbivision.com/2016/03/22/federation-taking-buyers-bordertown/|website=Television Business International|date=22 March 2016|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=Newby>{{cite web|last1=Newby|first1=Julian|title=MIPTV Fiction Wrap: Drama takes centre stage|url=https://mipblog.com/2016/05/miptv-wrap-drama/|website=MIPTrends|publisher=[[MIPTV|MIP Markets]]|date=May 11, 2016|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nInternational distribution rights were acquired from Federation Entertainment in October 2016 by [[Sky Deutschland]] for Germany, [[Canal+|CanalPlay]] for France, and [[Vlaamse Radio- en Televisieomroeporganisatie|VRT]] for Flanders (Dutch-speaking Belgium).<ref name=sells>{{cite web|last1=Pham|first1=Annika|title=Bordertown Sells to Germany-France-Belgium|url=http://www.nordiskfilmogtvfond.com/news/stories/bordertown-sells-to-germany-france-belgium|website=Nordisk Film & TV Fond|date=10 October 2016|accessdate=15 May 2018}}</ref> The series was sold to \"over 40 countries\".<ref name=Hannonen /> \n\n''Bordertown'' was renewed for a second season on 25 April 2017,<ref name=palaa>{{cite web|last1=Press Release|title=Sorjonen palaa Lappeenrantaan|url=https://www.epressi.com/tiedotteet/kotimaa/sorjonen-palaa-lappeenrantaan.html|website=[[Lappeenranta|City of Lappeenranta]]|date=25 April 2017|accessdate=19 August 2018|language=Finnish|trans-title=Sorjonen returns to Lappeenranta}}</ref> with Kuusniemi, Sinisalo, Susi, Ainali, and Villi also reprising their roles.<ref name=Hannonen /> Filming began in Lappeenranta on 8 August 2017, and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] in [[Helsinki]] on 7 November 2017.<ref name=phamS2>{{cite web|last1=Pham|first1=Annika|title=Summer shoot for Bordertown Season 2|url=http://www.nordiskfilmogtvfond.com/news/stories/summer-shoot-for-bordertown-season-2|website=Nordisk Film & TV Fond|date=2 May 2017|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=nordic2>{{cite web|title=Bordertown Begins Filming Season Two This August|url=https://nordicdrama.com/bordertown-begins-filming-season-two-this-august/|website=Nordic Drama|date=2 May 2017|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=R\u00f6mp\u00f6tti>{{cite web|last1=R\u00f6mp\u00f6tti|first1=Janne|title=Sorjosen tuotantotiimi aloitti uuden kauden kuvaukset Lappeenrannassa|url=https://uutisvuoksi.fi/uutiset/lahella/cf0ba30d-2f45-4f71-9aad-8991555314d7|website=Uutisvuoksi|date=10 August 2017|accessdate=19 August 2018|language=Finnish|trans-title=Sorjonen production team describes new season in Lappeenranta}}</ref>\n\nThe series was renewed for a third season in September 2018,<ref name=S3renew>{{cite web|last1=Maijala|first1=Juho|title=Sorjonen palaa viel\u00e4 Lappeenrantaan \u2014 Kolmas tuotantokausi n\u00e4ytt\u00e4\u00e4, millainen kaupunki on talvella|url=https://esaimaa.fi/uutiset/lahella/b33ee8da-696f-423c-9953-e847c9b56f1c|work=[[Etel\u00e4-Saimaa]]|date=26 September 2018|accessdate=25 March 2019|language=Finnish| trans-title=Sorjonen returns to Lappeenranta \u2013 the third season will show what kind of city it is in winter}}</ref> with filming starting on 13 December 2018.<ref name=S3film>{{cite web|last1=Pham|first1=Annika|title=Bordertown3 starts shooting for Yle|url=http://www.nordiskfilmogtvfond.com/news/stories/bordertown3-starts-shooting-for-yle|website=Nordisk Film & TV Fond|date=13 December 2018|accessdate=25 March 2019}}</ref> The season is set to premiere in December 2019, and it has been labelled as the final one.<ref name=S3film /><ref>[http://areena.yle.fi/1-50332439 Jokainen meist\u00e4 pystyy pahaan \u2013 Tulossa: Sorjonen 3.] Yle Areena (in Finnish).</ref>\n\n==Release==\n===Broadcast===\n''Bordertown'' premiered on [[Yle TV1]] on 16 October 2016.<ref name=McDonald>{{cite web|last1=Ainamo-McDonald|first1=Maria|title=Sorjonen \u2013 uusi kotimainen rikossarja|url=https://yle.fi/aihe/artikkeli/2016/08/23/sorjonen-uusi-kotimainen-rikossarja-alkaa-lokakuussa-ykkosella|website=[[Yle]]|date=23 August 2016|accessdate=1 December 2017|language=Finnish|trans-title=Sorjonen \u2013 a new domestic crime series}}</ref> The debut was watched by 1.1 million viewers and set a record for a Finnish series.<ref name=ZDFE>{{cite web|last1=Pham|first1=Annika|title=Finland's Fisher King signs first look deal with ZDFE|url=http://www.nordiskfilmogtvfond.com/news/stories/finlands-fisher-king-signs-first-look-deal-with-zdfe|website=Nordisk Film & TV Fond|date=20 October 2016|accessdate=19 August 2018}}</ref> The total viewership for Season 1 was an average of one million viewers.<ref name=Hannonen>{{cite web|last1=Hannonen|first1=Inka|title=Sorjosen toinen kausi menee ihon alle|url=https://yle.fi/aihe/artikkeli/2018/01/17/sorjosen-toinen-kausi-menee-ihon-alle|website=[[Yle]]|date=17 January 2018|accessdate=17 May 2018|language=Finnish|trans-title=The second season of Sorjonen goes under the skin}}</ref> \n\nSeason two premiered on 7 October 2018.<ref name=Yrttiaho>{{cite web|last1=Yrttiaho|first1=Tuomo|title=Kari Sorjonen palaa t\u00e4n\u00e4 iltana rikospaikalle \u2013 tv-sarjan vetovoima on yh\u00e4 Ville Virtasen varassa|url=http://www.hs.fi/kulttuuri/art-2000005854007.html|work=[[Helsingin Sanomat]]|publisher=[[Sanoma]]|date=7 October 2018|accessdate=7 November 2018|language=Finnish|trans-title=Kari Sorjonen returns to the crime scene tonight \u2013 the TV series attraction is still Ville Virtanen}}</ref> (It was originally scheduled to premiere on 14 October.<ref name=Imatralainen>{{cite web|title=Huippusuositun Sorjosen toinen kausi alkaa syksyll\u00e4 \u2013 ensimm\u00e4isen jakson esitysp\u00e4iv\u00e4 on selvill\u00e4|url=https://www.imatralainen.fi/artikkeli/601058-huippusuositun-sorjosen-toinen-kausi-alkaa-syksylla-ensimmaisen-jakson-esityspaiva|website=Imatralainen|date=22 January 2018|accessdate=19 August 2018|language=Finnish|trans-title=The second season of highly popular Sorjosen begins in fall \u2013 the date of first episode is set}}</ref>)\n\nSeason three will premiere on 1 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news | author=Slotte, Malin | title=Tio series att se fram emot i h\u00f6st | newspaper=Hufvudstadsbladet | date=26 August 2019 | pages=20\u201321 | language=Swedish | location=Helsingfors }}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n[[Netflix]] acquired rights in February 2017 to [[Streaming media|stream]] the series in the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, Norway, Sweden, Denmark, Iceland, Eastern Europe, Russia, and the Netherlands.<ref name=\u00c5kman>{{cite web|last1=\u00c5kman|first1=Erika|title=Suomalainen rikosdraama n\u00e4hd\u00e4\u00e4n nyt my\u00f6s USA:ssa! Netflix osti supersuositun Sorjosen|url=https://www.is.fi/viihde/art-2000005107913.html|work=[[Ilta-Sanomat]]|date=28 February 2017|accessdate=15 May 2018|language=Finnish|trans-title=Finnish crime drama is now seen also in the USA! Netflix acquires the super popular Sorjonen}}</ref> Streaming of Season 1 became available on 31 March 2017, followed by Season 2 on 2 February 2019 and season 3 on 11 May 2020. <ref>{{cite web|title=First Look at What\u2019s Coming to Netflix in May 2020|url=https://www.whats-on-netflix.com/coming-soon/whats-coming-to-netflix-in-may-2020-04-17/|website=What's on Netflix|date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nSeason 1 was released on [[DVD]] and [[Blu-ray]] in Germany by EuroVideo on 14 February 2019, followed by Season 2 on 11 April 2019<ref>{{cite web|title=Bordertown (Staffel 1)|url=https://ssl.ofdb.de/view.php?page=fassung_vorab&fid=293256&vid=92169|website=Online-Filmdatenbank|date=6 December 2018|accessdate=24 March 2019|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bordertown (Staffel 2)|url=https://ssl.ofdb.de/view.php?page=fassung_vorab&fid=293256&vid=93373|website=Online-Filmdatenbank|date=8 February 2019|accessdate=24 March 2019|language=German}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n''Bordertown'' won the 2017 [[Kultainen Venla|Golden Venla Awards]] for Best Drama Series, Best Actor (Ville Virtanen), and Best Actress (Anu Sinisalo).<ref name=sweep>{{cite web|last1=Pham|first1=Annika|title=Clean sweep for Bordertown at Finnish Emmys|url=http://www.nordiskfilmogtvfond.com/news/stories/clean-sweep-for-bordertown-at-finnish-emmys|website=Nordisk Film & TV Fond|date=16 January 2017|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=Vestrheim>{{cite web|last1=Vestrheim|first1=Emma|title=BORDERTOWN wins at the Finnish Emmy\u2019s|url=https://www.cinemascandinavia.com/bordertown-wins-at-the-finnish-emmys/|website=Cinema Scandinavia|date=17 January 2017|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Series overview==\n<!-- See [[MOS:TVOVERVIEW]] for template guidelines. -->\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| split = y\n\n| color1    = #8399af\n| link1     = <includeonly>List of Bordertown episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2016)\n| episodes1 = 11\n| start1    ={{Start date|2016|10|16|df=y}}\n| end1      ={{End date|2016|12|25|df=y}}\n\n| color2    = #465a68 \n| link2     = <includeonly>List of Bordertown episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2018)\n| episodes2 = 10\n| start2    = {{Start date|2018|10|7|df=y}}\n| end2      = {{End date|2018|12|9|df=y}}\n\n| color3    = #1C4492\n| link3     = <includeonly>List of Bordertown episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2019\u20132020)\n| episodes3 = 10\n| start3    ={{Start date|2019|12|1|df=y}}\n| end3      ={{End date|2020|2|2|df=y}}\n\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\n===Season 1 (2016)===\n{{Episode table|background=#8399af|overall=5|season=5|title=20|director=14|writer=25|airdate=17|country=Finland|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = The Dolls' House, part 1 &nbsp;(Nukkekoti, osa 1)\n| DirectedBy      = Miikko Oikkonen\n| WrittenBy       = Miikko Oikkonen, Atro Lahtela, Matti Laine, Antti Pesonen\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2016|10|16|df=y}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 8399af\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = The Dolls' House, part 2 &nbsp;(Nukkekoti, osa 2)\n| DirectedBy      = Miikko Oikkonen\n| WrittenBy       = Miikko Oikkonen, Atro Lahtela, Matti Laine, Antti Pesonen\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2016|10|23|df=y}} \n| LineColor       = 8399af\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = The Dolls' House, part 3 &nbsp;(Nukkekoti, osa 3)\n| DirectedBy      = Miikko Oikkonen\n| WrittenBy       = Miikko Oikkonen, Atro Lahtela, Matti Laine, Antti Pesonen\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2016|10|30|d